description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;NUTRITION &amp; DIETETIC SERVICES&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SENIOR SPECIALIST DIETITIAN (Gastroenterology / Surgery)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Permanent post – 37.5 hours per week&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you looking for a more specialised and challenging role in the areas of gastroenterology and surgery?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Would you like to work as part of an established MDT and be part of a large diverse dietetic department?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If yes, we are offering an opportunity to do both and would welcome an enthusiastic dietitian to come and join the team at South Tees Hospitals Nutrition and Dietetic service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post offers excellent opportunities to develop your skills and experience within the specialities of gastroenterology and general surgery. You will be given supervision, training and support from experienced Dietitians. The post holder will also be regularly involved in education of other health care professional and support workers. The post holder would be required to work within James Cook University Hospital and Friarage Hospital Northallerton, and may be required to work across Middlesbrough, Redcar and Cleveland community locality and Hambleton &amp; Richmond community locality. You must have HCPC registration.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have excellent clerical support and access to IT facilities within the department. Continual Professional Development is actively encouraged, as is participation in audit and evidence based practice. We have been Base Trainers for student dietitians for a number of years, currently taking A, B and C placement students.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The hospitals have an ideal location within easy reach of the East Coast, North Yorkshire Moors and Scotland.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Accommodation is available on site.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Charlotte Morrison (Senior Specialist Dietitian)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Email: charlotte.morrison1@nhs.net&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tel: 01642 854777&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
